The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Leak twist to the hockey drama
                                                                                                                       7                                      Leak twist to the hockey drama
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: The atmosphere surrounding Indian hockey turned murkier when an e-mail from an anonymous source leaked the minutes of the selection committee meeting held in Pune, on Saturday, for the Commonwealth and Asian Games.         
	While Hockey India (HI) said the team was yet to be announced, the e-mail has the 16-member squad, the names of the reserves and signatures of all the four selectors and two national coaches  Jose Brasa and Harendra Singh.         
	We are yet to declare the team, it may be done on Monday, said HI secretary general Narendra Batra. Asked about the e-mail, Batra simply said that he was not aware of it.         
	Former India captain Zafar Iqbal, one of the two government nominees in the selection committee, is currently in Pune and said he was in no position to comment on the subject. The meetings are still going on and the team will be announced by Hockey India, Iqbal said.         
	The e-mail from one Amit Das, who has declared himself as a hockey lover and well wisher, said that drag flicker Sandeep Singh has been inducted into the team after being dropped from the Azlan Shah squad. It also said that India will be going into the next two tournaments with only one goalkeeper.                                                                                                                     
